      "eroded remnants":                           { section:"reading", meaning:"tàn tích bị bào mòn, mảnh vỡ còn lại", type:"phrase", collocation:"eroded remnants of plastic waste", example:"What appear to be eroded remnants of plastic bags are among the most common pollutants found.", connotation:"negative" },
      "ecologically relevant questions":           { section:"reading", meaning:"câu hỏi có ý nghĩa sinh thái học", type:"phrase", collocation:"address ecologically relevant questions", example:"The research is praised for addressing ecologically relevant questions about real-world pollution levels.", connotation:"positive" },
      "the slow-moving effect":                    { section:"reading", meaning:"tác động diễn ra chậm, khó nhận thấy ngay", type:"phrase", collocation:"the slow-moving effect of pollution", example:"The slow-moving effect of plastic on ecosystems makes it difficult to draw clear cause-and-effect conclusions.", connotation:"negative" },
      "conjure up":                                { section:"reading", meaning:"gợi lên, khiến liên tưởng đến", type:"phrase", collocation:"conjure up images of", example:"The phrase 'ocean pollution' tends to conjure up images of seabirds trapped in plastic rings.", connotation:"neutral" },
      "strategically positioning":                 { section:"reading", meaning:"đặt vị trí một cách chiến lược, định vị khéo léo", type:"phrase", collocation:"strategically positioning research findings", example:"By strategically positioning their findings, scientists can shape public concern and policy responses.", connotation:"neutral" },
      "clearing up misperceptions":                { section:"reading", meaning:"xóa bỏ những hiểu lầm", type:"phrase", collocation:"clearing up misperceptions about a topic", example:"The review paper aims at clearing up misperceptions about the scale of the microplastic problem.", connotation:"positive" },
      "interrogating the existing scientific literature": { section:"reading", meaning:"xem xét kỹ / truy vấn tài liệu khoa học hiện có", type:"phrase", collocation:"interrogating the literature systematically", example:"By interrogating the existing scientific literature, the authors identified serious flaws in earlier studies.", connotation:"neutral" },
